Here's the approach:

### 1. Define each theme as a `ResourceDictionary`

Create three XAML files (e.g., `LightTheme.xaml`, `DarkTheme.xaml`, `HighContrastTheme.xaml`):

```xml
<!-- Resources/Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PageBackground">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryText">#1A1A1A</Color>
    <Color x:Key="Accent">#0078D4</Color>
    <!-- ... -->
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Use the **same keys** in all three dictionaries.

### 2. Swap the dictionary at runtime

Create a helper that merges the chosen dictionary into `App.Current.Resources`:

```csharp
public static class ThemeManager
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDicts = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;

        // Remove the old theme dictionary (always the last one added)
        if (mergedDicts.LastOrDefault() is ResourceDictionary old)
            mergedDicts.Remove(old);

        ResourceDictionary next = theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark         => new Resources.Themes.DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new Resources.Themes.HighContrastTheme(),
            _                     => new Resources.Themes.LightTheme(),
        };

        mergedDicts.Add(next);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }
}

public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }
```

### 3. Apply the saved theme on startup

In `App.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
    Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var theme);
    ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(theme);
}
```

### 4. Reference theme colours with `DynamicResource`

This is the key — `StaticResource` won't update when dictionaries change:

```xml
<ContentPage BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource PageBackground}">
    <Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryText}" Text="Hello" />
</ContentPage>
```

### 5. Settings page picker

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    var selected = (AppTheme)ThemePicker.SelectedIndex;
    ThemeManager.ApplyTheme(selected);
}
```

**Key points:**
- **`DynamicResource` everywhere** — otherwise swaps won't propagate.
- **Same keys** across all three dictionaries so every reference resolves.
- **`Preferences`** persists the choice across launches.
